      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHELLY'S ACE (7) missed a nose in a 50 at Murwillumbah and has been outgraded at the provincials since. Maps better today and this is winnable presented at best. AUSTRALASIA (1) recorded her maiden win four back and has been knocking on the door since in better grade. The near miss two back at Grafton was the best of them, and he tackles a shorter sprint off a 41-day freshen. Is ready to score again. SO BE INSPIRED (2) resumes and is at her best fresh. Has pieces of form good enough and keep onside. BEITSOO (5) resumes and disappointed in her three runs last preparation. She has raced well fresh and has a handy 2kg claim. Worth a betting watch. Ditto BARRON (3), who resumes and was beaten 1L here before the break. Has placed 2/6 first-up and is also in the mix.",
